EDUCATIONAL USE NOTICE:

This educational material is provided for non-commercial academic and 
professional development purposes. While the code/framework is MIT licensed,
please note:

1. ACADEMIC CITATIONS: When using this material in academic publications,
   please cite as:
   
   RK (2026). Behavioral Finance Lecture Framework: From Homo Economicus 
   to Homo Sapiens. GitHub. https://github.com/[your-username]/behavioral-finance-lecture

2. RESEARCH ATTRIBUTION: The theoretical foundations are based on published
   research by Kahneman, Tversky, Thaler, Ariely, and others. Appropriate
   academic citations are included throughout the materials.

3. COMMERCIAL WORKSHOPS: If you're conducting paid workshops using this
   material, please attribute the original framework and consider contributing
   improvements back to the repository.

4. MODIFICATIONS: You're encouraged to adapt this material for your specific
   context (different countries, industries, audiences). Please share your
   adaptations via pull requests so others can benefit.

